{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d6b327a8-d4fc-48f0-b190-2e6c9af1f311","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2, .NET Core 3.1, and .NET 5.0** — but importantly:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — End-of-life. MSTest v3 may still build, but it's no longer a supported runtime.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — End-of-life. Same concern.\n- **`net462`** — This meets the minimum .NET Framework requirement.\n\n**Key action items for a smooth migration:**\n\n1. **Update target frameworks** — Consider replacing `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with currently supported TFMs like `net6.0` or `net8.0`.\n2. **Use the MSTest meta-package** — In v3, the recommended approach is a single `MSTest` package reference instead of separate `TestFramework`/`TestAdapter` packages.\n3. **Review breaking changes** — MSTest v3 removes some deprecated APIs (e.g., `Assert.That`, some overloads of collection asserts) and changes default behavior (e.g., test class/method parallelization).\n\nWould you like me to update the `.csproj` to MSTest v3 with modernized target frameworks?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6df2f54a-b6e7-4ffb-87d6-29e3989ce29e","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"A416:28B932:13FA583:1590495:6A02EC53"},"id":"e32bbc9e-0434-49cc-86ba-f0d7d0190502","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:01:16.248Z","parentId":"3b45d7e0-8a81-4540-ad15-70cd75b5408a"}
